1
00:00:01,868 --> 00:00:03,804
Man:
<i>Your attention, everyone.</i>

2
00:00:03,804 --> 00:00:06,607
Having won all of her games
thus far in the tournament,

3
00:00:06,607 --> 00:00:09,175
Kurami Zell
awaits her next opponent.

4
00:00:09,175 --> 00:00:11,444
Is there anyone left
who is up to the challenge?

5
00:00:11,444 --> 00:00:14,180
Stephanie:
Sora, wait,
you can't be serious.

6
00:00:14,180 --> 00:00:15,616
You're gonna crash
the coronation?

7
00:00:15,616 --> 00:00:17,984
Hey, I just scored
a new life in this world.

8
00:00:17,984 --> 00:00:20,220
I can't lose my place
to live that quickly.

9
00:00:20,220 --> 00:00:22,455
Stephanie:
Yeah, but‐

10
00:00:22,455 --> 00:00:25,859
Now then, I think it's time
for me to become king

11
00:00:25,859 --> 00:00:28,529
and take back
our lost territory!

12
00:00:31,131 --> 00:00:34,134
<i>( theme song plays )</i>

13
00:02:04,324 --> 00:02:06,292
If there are no other
challengers,

14
00:02:06,292 --> 00:02:08,795
I shall proceed with the former
King's final wish

15
00:02:08,795 --> 00:02:12,165
and crown Kurami Zell
as our new ruler.

16
00:02:12,165 --> 00:02:14,735
<i>Should anyone wish to protest,</i>
<i>speak now‐</i>

17
00:02:14,735 --> 00:02:16,269
Sora:
<i>Objection!</i>

18
00:02:16,269 --> 00:02:17,337
( crowd gasps )

19
00:02:17,337 --> 00:02:21,074
You heard me!
( annunciated ) Objection!

20
00:02:21,074 --> 00:02:22,042
( chuckles )

21
00:02:22,042 --> 00:02:24,878
So, are you saying
that you request

22
00:02:24,878 --> 00:02:26,112
to be her next challenger?

23
00:02:26,112 --> 00:02:26,880
Yep.

24
00:02:26,880 --> 00:02:28,481
( crowd gasps )

25
00:02:28,481 --> 00:02:30,617
Despite your loss, you're still
desperate enough to win

26
00:02:30,617 --> 00:02:33,253
that you're sending
your butler after me?

27
00:02:33,253 --> 00:02:35,121
In case you hadn't noticed,
Little Princess,

28
00:02:35,121 --> 00:02:36,923
this isn't a playground.

29
00:02:36,923 --> 00:02:39,125
Yeah, and it's not the place
to hand over the throne

30
00:02:39,125 --> 00:02:42,028
to some con artist either,
especially one

31
00:02:42,028 --> 00:02:43,964
who's getting help
from another country.

32
00:02:43,964 --> 00:02:46,099
( all murmur )

33
00:02:46,099 --> 00:02:48,234
Sora:
Well, Shiro?
Shiro:
There's one.

34
00:02:48,234 --> 00:02:51,304
Anyone else
hiding their ears?
Nope.

35
00:02:51,304 --> 00:02:55,475
Kurami:
<i>That strange device,</i>
<i>they used it before.</i>

36
00:02:56,342 --> 00:02:57,644
And just what
do you mean by that?

37
00:02:57,644 --> 00:03:01,515
Oh, come on now, let's say,
for example, if the crown

38
00:03:01,515 --> 00:03:03,584
was given to someone
in cahoots with the Elves,

39
00:03:03,584 --> 00:03:06,687
Elkia would be pretty much
screwed, right guys?

40
00:03:06,687 --> 00:03:08,054
( all murmur )

41
00:03:08,054 --> 00:03:10,490
What exactly
is the meaning of this?

42
00:03:10,490 --> 00:03:12,826
So what, is this
your pathetic attempt

43
00:03:12,826 --> 00:03:13,660
at accusing me
of cheating?

44
00:03:13,660 --> 00:03:17,330
Calm down. I clearly
said "for example."

45
00:03:17,330 --> 00:03:20,867
Or maybe it actually rings
a bell for you, huh?

46
00:03:20,867 --> 00:03:23,604
Fine then, since
you've made your objection,

47
00:03:23,604 --> 00:03:26,907
I suppose I'll have
to humor you with a game,
is what you want?

48
00:03:26,907 --> 00:03:29,109
Yay! Thanks, Madam.
I'd really appreciate that.

49
00:03:29,109 --> 00:03:30,410
But, but Miss‐

50
00:03:30,410 --> 00:03:32,445
One thing,
if we're playing poker again,

51
00:03:32,445 --> 00:03:35,481
maybe this time, you should ask
your friend to leave.

52
00:03:35,481 --> 00:03:38,652
I'm sorry to have
to do this, but...

53
00:03:38,652 --> 00:03:40,854
There's an elf here!
What the hell's going on?!

54
00:03:40,854 --> 00:03:44,190
So these two witches
were working together?!

55
00:03:44,190 --> 00:03:45,191
Nothing to say?

56
00:03:45,191 --> 00:03:48,829
The pretty swindler's gonna
abandon her partner in crime?

57
00:03:48,829 --> 00:03:49,896
How cruel.

58
00:03:50,631 --> 00:03:51,464
I get it.

59
00:03:51,464 --> 00:03:53,534
So you've teamed up
with some random elf

60
00:03:53,534 --> 00:03:56,503
to try to make me out
to be an enemy of Imanity,
is that it?

61
00:03:56,503 --> 00:03:59,740
(chuckles)
Pretty good deflection,
I must admit.

62
00:03:59,740 --> 00:04:03,877
Perhaps it's best you left.
Elves have no place here.

63
00:04:06,012 --> 00:04:07,648
There.
You satisfied?

64
00:04:07,648 --> 00:04:09,750
Sure am.
Ready to play now?

65
00:04:09,750 --> 00:04:13,019
As you're likely aware
as stated by the pledges,

66
00:04:13,019 --> 00:04:14,888
I get to decide the game.

67
00:04:14,888 --> 00:04:15,722
But no need to worry.

68
00:04:15,722 --> 00:04:17,891
I'll choose a game
where cheating is impossible.

69
00:04:17,891 --> 00:04:20,460
Pledge number five,
the challenged party

70
00:04:20,460 --> 00:04:23,597
has the right to decide
the content of the game, huh?

71
00:04:23,597 --> 00:04:25,265
Dang, no poker this time?

72
00:04:25,265 --> 00:04:26,833
Well, since
I'm such a nice guy,

73
00:04:26,833 --> 00:04:29,069
I won't bother asking
about your reasons.

74
00:04:29,069 --> 00:04:31,104
Say cheese!

75
00:04:31,104 --> 00:04:31,638
Hmm.

76
00:04:31,638 --> 00:04:33,640
Wow, you're not really
photogenic.

77
00:04:33,640 --> 00:04:36,910
If you smiled once in a while,
you'd be a lot cuter.

78
00:04:36,910 --> 00:04:40,313
We'll hold the game
in another venue.

79
00:04:40,313 --> 00:04:43,216
I'll call for you
once it's prepared.

80
00:04:43,216 --> 00:04:45,986
Stephanie:
Wait, you're telling me
she used magic to beat me?!

81
00:04:45,986 --> 00:04:48,421
Hey, will you keep it down
a little bit?

82
00:04:48,421 --> 00:04:50,223
That's right,
Shiro and I both noticed

83
00:04:50,223 --> 00:04:52,058
when we saw your game
at the tavern.

84
00:04:52,058 --> 00:04:53,393
Don't you mean
I noticed?

85
00:04:53,393 --> 00:04:55,161
Don't sweat
the small stuff, Sis.

86
00:04:55,161 --> 00:04:56,530
So that's what
it does then,

87
00:04:56,530 --> 00:04:58,131
that special secret tool
of yours

88
00:04:58,131 --> 00:04:59,533
is for detecting magic,
isn't it?

89
00:04:59,533 --> 00:05:02,468
So how'd they do it?
What kind of magic
did that Elf use?

90
00:05:02,468 --> 00:05:04,170
No idea, sugar pants.

91
00:05:04,170 --> 00:05:05,371
( yelps )

92
00:05:05,371 --> 00:05:07,107
Magic's amazing, isn't it?

93
00:05:07,107 --> 00:05:09,475
If you could change cards
when they're face‐down,

94
00:05:09,475 --> 00:05:10,877
we could never prove it.

95
00:05:10,877 --> 00:05:12,445
<i>Sora:</i>
<i>Under normal circumstances,</i>

96
00:05:12,445 --> 00:05:14,848
<i>there's essentially</i>
<i>no way to beat her.</i>

97
00:05:14,848 --> 00:05:17,684
Shiro:
Why do you think we didn't
challenge her before?

98
00:05:17,684 --> 00:05:21,988
Look, Steph, I'll break it down
as simply as I can for you.

99
00:05:21,988 --> 00:05:25,491
<i>Sora:</i>
<i>First of all, this round‐robin</i>
<i>style tournament to become king</i>

100
00:05:25,491 --> 00:05:27,661
<i>is pretty jacked up</i>
<i>to begin with.</i>

101
00:05:27,661 --> 00:05:29,996
<i>Let's say a country partners</i>
<i>up with an Imanity</i>

102
00:05:29,996 --> 00:05:31,632
<i>with the promise</i>
<i>of becoming king.</i>

103
00:05:31,632 --> 00:05:33,767
<i>From there on, they can</i>
<i>manipulate the games.</i>

104
00:05:33,767 --> 00:05:35,235
<i>They'll play against</i>
<i>other Imanities</i>

105
00:05:35,235 --> 00:05:38,404
<i>who also can't detect magic,</i>
<i>so it's a guaranteed win.</i>

106
00:05:38,404 --> 00:05:39,906
<i>Now that they've got</i>
<i>a puppet king,</i>

107
00:05:39,906 --> 00:05:42,108
<i>they can pretty much do</i>
<i>whatever the heck</i>

108
00:05:42,108 --> 00:05:43,243
<i>they want with Elkia.</i>

109
00:05:43,243 --> 00:05:43,877
<i>The plan's so simple,</i>

110
00:05:43,877 --> 00:05:47,714
<i>even a baby</i>
<i>could've dreamt it up.</i>

111
00:05:47,714 --> 00:05:51,251
But then, guess what the other
countries start thinking.

112
00:05:51,251 --> 00:05:53,319
So what do you think
we should do now?

113
00:05:53,319 --> 00:05:56,857
Kurami:
There's nothing to worry about.
He's just another Imanity.

114
00:05:56,857 --> 00:05:59,125
Even if he's probably getting
help from another race,

115
00:05:59,125 --> 00:06:00,426
so am I.

116
00:06:00,426 --> 00:06:03,163
It's not like
I didn't expect this.

117
00:06:03,163 --> 00:06:06,299
Kurami, do you really think
you'll be able to handle

118
00:06:06,299 --> 00:06:07,801
playing the games
without me?

119
00:06:07,801 --> 00:06:11,738
Kurami:
(scoffs)
<i>I'll be fine.</i>

120
00:06:11,738 --> 00:06:13,707
Stephanie:
So you really think
it's possible that Kurami

121
00:06:13,707 --> 00:06:15,542
has convinced herself
that we're getting help

122
00:06:15,542 --> 00:06:16,710
from another race?

123
00:06:16,710 --> 00:06:19,580
Sora:
Yeah, by now
she probably realizes

124
00:06:19,580 --> 00:06:21,181
that Elkia is caught
in a diplomatic war

125
00:06:21,181 --> 00:06:23,349
between other nations.
Steph:
Then we're in luck.

126
00:06:23,349 --> 00:06:25,351
She can't use magic again
since she'll think

127
00:06:25,351 --> 00:06:27,854
other races will be watching,
ah‐ha!

128
00:06:27,854 --> 00:06:29,289
So she'll have to play fair
and square,

129
00:06:29,289 --> 00:06:32,125
and it'll be impossible
for her to cheat using magic!

130
00:06:32,125 --> 00:06:34,561
(groan)
It's all sunshine
and flowers in your head!

131
00:06:34,561 --> 00:06:36,663
Just crush my optimism,
why don't you?

132
00:06:36,663 --> 00:06:38,431
I'm sure they expected it.

133
00:06:38,431 --> 00:06:39,966
Another country
was bound to intervene.

134
00:06:39,966 --> 00:06:41,768
But I'll bet this time,
they'll use some spell

135
00:06:41,768 --> 00:06:43,403
or mind trick
we can't detect.

136
00:06:43,403 --> 00:06:45,305
If we can't even spot
their regular tricks,

137
00:06:45,305 --> 00:06:46,573
then we're totally doomed.

138
00:06:46,573 --> 00:06:48,742
They'll lay out a game
that looks fair on the surface

139
00:06:48,742 --> 00:06:51,444
so it doesn't seem
completely hopeless.

140
00:06:51,444 --> 00:06:53,780
But they won't use
their magic directly on us,

141
00:06:53,780 --> 00:06:55,616
like screwing with
our vision or memories,

142
00:06:55,616 --> 00:06:57,183
because it'll be too obvious.

143
00:06:57,183 --> 00:06:57,651
In other words,

144
00:06:57,651 --> 00:06:59,853
it won't be completely
impossible to win.

145
00:06:59,853 --> 00:07:02,288
So is that supposed
to make me feel better?

146
00:07:02,288 --> 00:07:04,390
As long as there
is some path to victory,

147
00:07:04,390 --> 00:07:05,325
no matter how small...

148
00:07:05,325 --> 00:07:09,129
Then you can bet your sweet
fanny that Blank won't lose.

149
00:07:09,129 --> 00:07:10,230
There you go.

150
00:07:10,230 --> 00:07:12,533
( chokes )
Hmm?

151
00:07:15,068 --> 00:07:16,737
Kurami:
<i>Let me be honest with you guys.</i>

152
00:07:16,737 --> 00:07:18,905
<i>The only reason I struck</i>
<i>a deal with the Elves</i>

153
00:07:18,905 --> 00:07:21,542
<i>was to secure a place</i>
<i>for Imanity to live</i>

154
00:07:21,542 --> 00:07:23,143
<i>after I've won the tournament.</i>

155
00:07:23,143 --> 00:07:25,812
Once we've acquired
a fair amount of territory,

156
00:07:25,812 --> 00:07:26,913
I'll cut ties
with the Elves for good.

157
00:07:26,913 --> 00:07:29,315
Sora:
Oh, jeez.
Shiro:
Oh, jeez.

158
00:07:29,315 --> 00:07:30,083
I know she's dumb,

159
00:07:30,083 --> 00:07:32,586
but you didn't have
to say it out loud, Sis.

160
00:07:32,586 --> 00:07:33,954
So you know,
we might be spies,

161
00:07:33,954 --> 00:07:36,557
and yet you're still
telling us your plan‐ cuckoo!

162
00:07:36,557 --> 00:07:39,626
Think about it,
the only way for us to survive

163
00:07:39,626 --> 00:07:41,695
is to win the right
to live under the protection

164
00:07:41,695 --> 00:07:44,164
of a powerful nation,
give up on games,

165
00:07:44,164 --> 00:07:45,732
and close off our borders.

166
00:07:45,732 --> 00:07:49,035
There's no other choice,
right, Little Princess?

167
00:07:49,035 --> 00:07:51,838
You of all people
should understand that.

168
00:07:51,838 --> 00:07:52,839
Well, I‐

169
00:07:52,839 --> 00:07:55,576
Kurami:
<i>What's more, Elven Gard</i>
<i>currently comprises</i>

170
00:07:55,576 --> 00:07:57,410
<i>the largest nation</i>
<i>in the world,</i>

171
00:07:57,410 --> 00:08:00,146
<i>and not a single race has been</i>
<i>able to defeat their magic.</i>

172
00:08:00,146 --> 00:08:02,215
<i>It's impossible</i>
<i>for you to beat me,</i>

173
00:08:02,215 --> 00:08:05,451
<i>so it's in your best interest</i>
<i>just to withdraw from the game.</i>

174
00:08:05,451 --> 00:08:07,387
I swear to all Imanity
that I won't let

175
00:08:07,387 --> 00:08:09,389
the Elves make me
their puppet.

176
00:08:09,389 --> 00:08:10,757
Sora...

177
00:08:10,757 --> 00:08:12,626
Okay, not a bad plan.

178
00:08:12,626 --> 00:08:15,495
We live quietly under
another nation's wing.

179
00:08:15,495 --> 00:08:17,230
Sounds pretty promising.

180
00:08:17,230 --> 00:08:17,764
Doesn't it?

181
00:08:17,764 --> 00:08:19,265
That's why you should withdraw‐

182
00:08:19,265 --> 00:08:21,568
But I refuse!

183
00:08:21,568 --> 00:08:24,004
You know one of the things
Blank loves best?

184
00:08:24,004 --> 00:08:25,872
Both:
Telling people "no"
and shutting them down

185
00:08:25,872 --> 00:08:27,708
when they think
they've already run the game,

186
00:08:27,708 --> 00:08:30,744
then telling them
they can go screw themselves!

187
00:08:32,846 --> 00:08:34,380
Number four
on our list of things

188
00:08:34,380 --> 00:08:35,949
we always wanted
to say someday!

189
00:08:35,949 --> 00:08:39,052
Sweet, we did it!
Yeah, we're so awesome.

190
00:08:39,052 --> 00:08:42,889
It appears that reasoning
with you is a waste of time.

191
00:08:42,889 --> 00:08:46,259
Then just as you wish,
I will make you yield by force.

192
00:08:47,027 --> 00:08:49,162
<i>It's your funeral.</i>

193
00:08:51,464 --> 00:08:52,899
But, Sora, why not?
Why what?

194
00:08:52,899 --> 00:08:55,168
That plan she was
just talking about,

195
00:08:55,168 --> 00:08:55,936
it kind of makes sense

196
00:08:55,936 --> 00:08:57,904
given the desperate
situation we're in.

197
00:08:57,904 --> 00:09:00,607
(sighs)
Steph, look, don't you think
it's about time

198
00:09:00,607 --> 00:09:03,309
you learned to stop being
so trusting of people?

199
00:09:03,309 --> 00:09:05,111
For one,
what proof do we have

200
00:09:05,111 --> 00:09:07,013
that anything she said
is even true?

201
00:09:07,013 --> 00:09:09,883
Second, if she's so confident
that she can win,

202
00:09:09,883 --> 00:09:12,519
then why did she ask us
to withdraw?

203
00:09:12,519 --> 00:09:15,021
And third, even
if anything she said was true,

204
00:09:15,021 --> 00:09:16,523
I could be a spy
from another country,

205
00:09:16,523 --> 00:09:19,292
and anyone dumb enough to spill
their plan shouldn't be ruling.

206
00:09:19,292 --> 00:09:22,696
Okay, fourth, if we play along
and she does any digging on us,

207
00:09:22,696 --> 00:09:25,666
we're totally screwed,
<i>comprende?</i>

208
00:09:25,666 --> 00:09:27,333
Wow, you really
put a lot of thought

209
00:09:27,333 --> 00:09:28,869
into that speech,
didn't you?

210
00:09:28,869 --> 00:09:33,039
(sighs)
Look, those are just details.

211
00:09:33,907 --> 00:09:35,909
Don't sell humanity short.

212
00:09:35,909 --> 00:09:37,811
We're better than that.

213
00:09:47,621 --> 00:09:48,789
Chess?

214
00:09:48,789 --> 00:09:50,657
That's right,
but this isn't

215
00:09:50,657 --> 00:09:52,025
your normal game of chess.

216
00:09:52,025 --> 00:09:54,027
<i>Each piece</i>
<i>has a will of its own.</i>

217
00:09:54,027 --> 00:09:56,763
<i>Give them orders,</i>
<i>and they'll move.</i>

218
00:09:56,763 --> 00:09:59,633
<i>Think of them</i>
<i>as your own personal army.</i>

219
00:09:59,633 --> 00:10:01,267
( chuckles )

220
00:10:01,267 --> 00:10:05,005
So that's how this works.
Shiro, what's the plan?

221
00:10:05,005 --> 00:10:09,710
Chess is no different
than a game of tic‐tac‐toe.

222
00:10:09,710 --> 00:10:13,013
So, like, it's cool
if we rotate mid‐game right?

223
00:10:13,013 --> 00:10:14,915
Sora‐
I'm not trying
to be difficult,

224
00:10:14,915 --> 00:10:17,117
but the two of us count
as a single player.

225
00:10:17,117 --> 00:10:19,553
Plus you seem to be pretty
familiar with this game already

226
00:10:19,553 --> 00:10:22,689
whereas we don't
have a clue. Cheese!

227
00:10:22,689 --> 00:10:24,390
Kurami:
<i>They'll never figure this out.</i>

228
00:10:24,390 --> 00:10:26,226
You may do whatever you wish.

229
00:10:26,226 --> 00:10:29,095
But why? Do you think
I'm going to lose?

230
00:10:29,095 --> 00:10:31,097
Hey,
don't take it personally.

231
00:10:31,097 --> 00:10:35,437
Hell would freeze over before
you ever lost a game of chess.

232
00:10:35,437 --> 00:10:38,371
<i>But this isn't</i>
<i>the game you're used to.</i>

233
00:10:38,371 --> 00:10:41,908
And don't forget, combined,
we're a single player.

